### 5. UNDERLYING PARSERS

**Location:** `/src/interchange/` directory

Available parsers:
- `/src/interchange/json.zig` - Handles JSON and JSONC (TSConfig parsing)
- `/src/interchange/json5.zig` - JSON5 parser
- `/src/interchange/toml.zig` - TOML parser (with sub-module `/src/interchange/toml/lexer.zig`)
- `/src/interchange/yaml.zig` - YAML parser

**Pattern for implementing parse function:**
```zig
var arena = bun.ArenaAllocator.init(globalThis.allocator());
const allocator = arena.allocator();
defer arena.deinit();

var ast_memory_allocator = bun.handleOom(allocator.create(ast.ASTMemoryAllocator));
var ast_scope = ast_memory_allocator.enter(allocator);
defer ast_scope.exit();

var log = logger.Log.init(default_allocator);
defer log.deinit();

const input_value = callframe.argument(0);
if (input_value.isEmptyOrUndefinedOrNull()) {
    return globalThis.throwInvalidArguments("Expected a string to parse", .{});
}

var input_slice = try input_value.toSlice(globalThis, bun.default_allocator);
defer input_slice.deinit();

const source = &logger.Source.initPathString("input.format", input_slice.slice());
const parse_result = PARSER.parse(source, &log, allocator, ...) catch |err| {
    if (err == error.StackOverflow) {
        return globalThis.throwStackOverflow();
    }
    return globalThis.throwValue(try log.toJS(globalThis, default_allocator, "Failed to parse format"));
};

return parse_result.toJS(allocator, globalThis) catch |err| switch (err) {
    error.OutOfMemory => return error.OutOfMemory,
    error.JSError => return error.JSError,
    error.JSTerminated => return error.JSTerminated,
    else => unreachable,
};
```

### 6. KEY DIFFERENCES BY FORMAT

**JSONC vs JSON5 vs YAML comparison:**

| Feature | JSONC | JSON5 | YAML |
|---------|-------|-------|------|
| Parse only | ✓ | ✗ (has stringify) | ✗ (has stringify) |
| Stringify | ✗ | ✓ (full impl) | ✓ (full impl) |
| Circular ref detection | ✗ | ✓ | ✓ |
| Space param support | ✗ | ✓ (stringify) | ✓ (stringify) |
| Object count hint | 1 | 2 | 2 |
| Array input handling | ✗ | ✗ | ✓ (TypedArrays) |

### 7. NO EXISTING INI SUPPORT

- No INI files or tests found in the codebase
- No `src/interchange/ini.zig` parser exists
- No npm INI package shim found in `src/js/thirdparty/`
- This is a new namespace to be implemented

